WEBVTT

00:05.500 --> 00:07.083
Previously on "Billions"...

00:07.166 --> 00:09.041
You know
those poison-tip arrows

00:09.125 --> 00:11.000
that go through one guy
and kill another?

00:11.083 --> 00:13.250
As long as it
doesn't come from you.

00:13.333 --> 00:14.750
You get someone else
to ask her.

00:14.834 --> 00:15.959
Won't track back to me.

00:16.041 --> 00:18.792
You come through for me,
I'll pay off your house.

00:18.875 --> 00:20.625
People are getting sick
on Ice Juice.

00:20.709 --> 00:22.166
Freezing the assets?

00:22.250 --> 00:25.083
Now, that's an Ivan Koloff bear
hug you're putting on the man.

00:25.166 --> 00:27.083
You're squeezing the breath
out of him.

00:27.166 --> 00:29.000
But now you owe me.

00:29.083 --> 00:31.041
A favor to be named later.

00:31.125 --> 00:33.750
Back channeling, patronage.
I lost my taste for it.

00:33.834 --> 00:35.792
Just don't forget, it was the
back channels and deal-making

00:35.875 --> 00:38.250
that put you
in that position.

00:38.333 --> 00:40.834
Remind me again, and it's
the last meal we share.

00:40.917 --> 00:42.917
It is still Axe Capital,

00:43.000 --> 00:45.291
no matter who's making
the day-to-day decisions.

00:45.375 --> 00:46.625
Are you sure?

00:46.709 --> 00:48.959
I know it's Axe's faith that
confers value on me

00:49.041 --> 00:50.041
until I have
a track record of my own.

00:50.125 --> 00:53.333
Unless it becomes necessary,
I will not leave.

00:53.417 --> 00:55.875
I'm holding in my hand
Robert Axelrod's signature

00:55.959 --> 00:58.125
relinquishing his ability
to trade securities.

00:58.208 --> 01:00.208
Well...

01:00.291 --> 01:03.208
ol' Samson
got a real buzz cut.

01:09.875 --> 01:13.125
♪ dramatic music  ♪

01:13.208 --> 01:17.166
♪♪♪

01:17.250 --> 01:21.208
♪♪♪

01:21.291 --> 01:25.166
♪♪♪

01:25.250 --> 01:27.959
♪ Counting Crows
"Round Here"  ♪

01:28.041 --> 01:31.667
♪♪♪

01:31.750 --> 01:35.542
♪♪♪

01:35.625 --> 01:39.166
♪ Step out the front door
like a ghost into a fog ♪

01:39.250 --> 01:42.500
♪ Where no one notices
the contrast ♪

01:42.583 --> 01:44.500
♪ Of white on white ♪

01:44.583 --> 01:49.959
♪ In between the moon and you,
the angels get a better view ♪

01:50.041 --> 01:54.500
♪ Of the crumbling difference
between wrong and right ♪

01:54.583 --> 01:56.166
♪ Well, I walk in the air ♪

01:56.250 --> 01:58.333
-Hold on.
-♪ Between the rain ♪

01:58.417 --> 02:00.417
♪ Through myself
and back again ♪

02:00.500 --> 02:01.959
♪ Where? ♪

02:02.041 --> 02:04.834
♪ I don't know ♪

02:04.917 --> 02:07.500
♪ Maria says she's dying ♪

02:07.583 --> 02:09.041
Bobby. Are you okay?

02:09.125 --> 02:11.208
I went down
to the crossroads.

02:11.291 --> 02:12.417
What?

02:12.500 --> 02:13.250
I made a mistake.

02:13.333 --> 02:18.166
The deal.
I can't do it--not trade.

02:18.250 --> 02:19.542
I've worked my entire life

02:19.625 --> 02:23.875
putting myself in a position
where I would be truly free--

02:23.959 --> 02:26.458
no limits, nothing
I couldn't do.

02:26.542 --> 02:28.208
And with one signature,

02:28.291 --> 02:30.542
I've stripped myself
of all of that.

02:30.625 --> 02:32.208
It wasn't the signature
that did it.

02:32.291 --> 02:34.375
It was the living like
there were no rules.

02:34.458 --> 02:36.375
That's what made
the signature necessary.

02:36.458 --> 02:38.375
Wendy

02:38.458 --> 02:40.417
Yeah. Don't wake up
the kids.

02:40.500 --> 02:43.125
I'll be right up.

02:43.208 --> 02:44.041
I can't do this now.

02:44.125 --> 02:46.875
Realize that limits,

02:47.000 --> 02:48.750
constraints,
they can be useful.

02:48.834 --> 02:51.000
Letting someone else
run Axe Capital gives you

02:51.083 --> 02:53.834
a chance to realign
who you are.

02:53.917 --> 02:57.917
To get good at letting go.
Which is a different

02:58.000 --> 03:00.959
kind of freedom. A more
powerful kind of freedom.

03:01.041 --> 03:02.000
Now go to sleep.

03:02.083 --> 03:05.583
Even if it were a good idea,
which it's not,

03:05.667 --> 03:08.709
there is nothing you can do
to regain control at this hour.

03:11.166 --> 03:12.625
♪ dramatic music  ♪

03:12.709 --> 03:17.583
♪♪♪

03:17.667 --> 03:23.542
♪♪♪

03:23.625 --> 03:28.500
♪♪♪

03:28.583 --> 03:33.458
♪♪♪

03:33.542 --> 03:38.458
♪♪♪

03:38.542 --> 03:40.625
We need to meet.

03:40.709 --> 03:43.417
These fuckers can
take away my ability to trade

03:43.500 --> 03:45.291
but not my ability to see.

03:45.375 --> 03:48.000
Insightful guy like you,
how you gonna turn it off?

03:48.083 --> 03:49.417
I'm not. I can't.
I don't want to.

03:49.500 --> 03:52.333
If you can't trade on
the insights, who can?

03:52.417 --> 03:56.125
Only those who I have
reason to trust absolutely.

03:56.208 --> 03:58.291
-And that's me.
-It better be.

03:58.375 --> 04:01.750
Because no one can know I'm
behind any  of these trades.

04:01.834 --> 04:04.000
Well, our doors wouldn't
be open if it wasn't for your,

04:04.083 --> 04:07.291
um, let's say goodwill.

04:07.375 --> 04:09.792
And when we're done,
those doors are gonna open

04:09.875 --> 04:11.709
on to a much bigger shop.

04:11.792 --> 04:13.750
Been hoping
to hear from you.

04:13.834 --> 04:14.709
I've been wanting to expand,

04:14.792 --> 04:16.667
but I've never been
great at the raise.

04:16.750 --> 04:20.208
That'll no longer be a problem
for Old Oaks Investments.

04:20.291 --> 04:21.834
Your money is
always good here.

04:21.917 --> 04:24.458
You can't direct funds,
so how's this work?

04:24.542 --> 04:27.208
Let's dive the fuck in.

04:27.291 --> 04:29.709
I'll be in touch.

04:29.792 --> 04:31.709
♪ dramatic music  ♪

04:34.250 --> 04:35.667
So, this is
the way it's done?

04:35.750 --> 04:37.667
Yeah.

04:37.750 --> 04:39.834
And there's really nothing
we can do but--

04:39.917 --> 04:42.166
Hope the wheel
of fate favors us.

04:42.250 --> 04:44.500
♪ dramatic music  ♪

04:44.583 --> 04:48.333
Welcome to old New York,
where judicial assignment's

04:48.417 --> 04:50.959
still determined by
the spin of a wheel.

04:51.041 --> 04:53.166
Hey, it beats having
Chief Judge Morgenstern

04:53.250 --> 04:55.041
make 'em after a long night
of gin at the goulash joint.

04:55.125 --> 04:58.583
-Both.

05:01.458 --> 05:05.291
For the United States
v. Robert Axelrod...

05:08.625 --> 05:11.041
...Judge Leonard Funt.

05:14.375 --> 05:15.583
Do I have to say it?

05:15.667 --> 05:16.542
You really don't.

05:16.625 --> 05:18.375
You just got Funted.

05:18.458 --> 05:20.208
Ha!

05:20.291 --> 05:24.000
[laughing continues
in distance]

05:24.083 --> 05:26.333
How bad is this?

05:26.417 --> 05:29.625
Funt is a true believer in
the power of a free market.

05:29.709 --> 05:31.375
Old school Libertarian.

05:31.458 --> 05:33.000
He's the best friend
Bobby Axelrod

05:33.083 --> 05:34.917
could have on the bench.

05:35.000 --> 05:35.959
Well, if Connerty
builds the case right,

05:36.041 --> 05:39.500
the judge doesn't matter.

05:39.583 --> 05:41.250
Wrong.

05:41.333 --> 05:44.250
You need to find a way
to get Funt off the case.

05:44.333 --> 05:46.333
So the wheel spits
out another name?

05:46.417 --> 05:48.250
No. Only one spin,

05:48.333 --> 05:51.625
then it's up to
Chief Judge Morgenstern.

05:51.709 --> 05:53.583
The other judges lobby him,
depending on if they want

05:53.667 --> 05:58.041
on or off. So you need
to stunt that process.

05:58.125 --> 05:59.959
That is tampering
twice over.

06:00.041 --> 06:01.959
No. It's finesse.

06:04.917 --> 06:09.000
I don't break promises,
so our unappetizing deal holds.

06:09.083 --> 06:11.750
-Mm.
-But it will not expand.

06:11.834 --> 06:13.959
Fate has dealt our hand.

06:14.041 --> 06:16.417
Now we play it.

06:21.542 --> 06:25.291
♪♪♪

06:25.375 --> 06:27.500
Chuck.

06:27.583 --> 06:30.333
What couldn't be talked
about on the phone?

06:32.041 --> 06:35.542
We got judge-fucked
in the Axelrod case.

06:35.625 --> 06:39.041
And, uh, I don't mean
"We, the people," I mean--

06:39.125 --> 06:42.291
We. Our family.

06:45.542 --> 06:47.917
-Fuck.
-Yeah.

06:49.500 --> 06:52.250
We need a judge who
believes that the rich

06:52.333 --> 06:54.709
have gotten away with
too much for too long.

06:54.792 --> 06:58.875
And one who won't allow Axelrod
to create a distraction

06:58.959 --> 07:01.583
by alleging I set up
a roach motel and lured him in.

07:01.667 --> 07:04.375
Axe can't do that without
essentially admitting his guilt.

07:04.458 --> 07:05.834
I know.

07:05.917 --> 07:09.834
That's one of the things
keeping me up at night.

07:09.917 --> 07:14.000
You know what I risked--
what I gave up--to get him.

07:15.583 --> 07:18.458
What would
he give to get me?

07:20.375 --> 07:22.375
Everything.

07:23.542 --> 07:27.667
Well, the judge we drew
is Leonard Edward Funt.

07:27.750 --> 07:29.834
Isn't that good news?
Doesn't he owe you--

07:29.917 --> 07:31.000
Yes, there is a debt.

07:31.083 --> 07:35.375
I once did him a kindness.
But back then, during a case,

07:35.458 --> 07:40.458
I tried to allude to
the favor in conference,

07:40.542 --> 07:43.917
and that man hammered me
for even hinting at it.

07:46.458 --> 07:49.667
Seemed to grow
larger as he talked,

07:49.750 --> 07:51.792
the way some men can
when they're not pretending

07:51.875 --> 07:55.625
to dignity and honor but they're
actually made of the stuff.

07:55.709 --> 07:56.834
You withdrew
the request?

07:56.917 --> 07:58.542
I did.

07:58.625 --> 08:02.417
And I fear it would
be even worse today.

08:02.500 --> 08:04.917
See, if he wouldn't return a
favor back when it was fresh,

08:05.000 --> 08:05.834
why would he do so now?

08:05.917 --> 08:08.458
But that's not what
happened, is it?

08:08.542 --> 08:10.125
He didn't actually refuse.
He didn't say no.

08:10.208 --> 08:12.500
Not in so many words.

08:12.583 --> 08:14.667
What he did was: spare
himself the question

08:14.750 --> 08:17.291
by putting a tougher
one to you.

08:17.375 --> 08:20.375
It's about will, Chuck.

08:20.458 --> 08:22.709
Impose your will on him
until he does what

08:22.792 --> 08:25.709
he needs to
and repays the debt.

08:27.500 --> 08:30.458
Why, you are a marvel.

08:34.500 --> 08:36.625
Go.

08:36.709 --> 08:38.750
Do what you have to do.

08:38.834 --> 08:42.041
♪ dramatic music  ♪

08:42.125 --> 08:45.875
♪♪♪

08:45.959 --> 08:49.583
♪♪♪

08:49.667 --> 08:52.417
I've recently invested
nine billion of Axe Cap's money

08:52.500 --> 08:55.125
back into the market. In phases.
And now when it's time

08:55.208 --> 08:57.041
for the next phase,
another two billion--

08:57.125 --> 08:58.375
You can't.

08:58.458 --> 09:00.166
Why?

09:00.250 --> 09:03.792
There's a velvet rope
around it. So to speak.

09:03.875 --> 09:06.083
What's actually
around it?

09:06.166 --> 09:09.375
A directive from Axe that
the money remain untouched.

09:09.458 --> 09:11.000
Is he considering
moving the funds

09:11.083 --> 09:13.041
or deploying
them elsewhere?

09:13.792 --> 09:16.333
Never mind.
You don't know.

09:16.417 --> 09:17.125
Don't I?

09:17.208 --> 09:19.709
Maybe Axe is hedging.

09:19.792 --> 09:20.959
Against the main fund?

09:21.041 --> 09:22.458
Against you.

09:22.542 --> 09:27.125
♪ dramatic music  ♪

09:29.166 --> 09:32.792
♪♪♪

09:32.875 --> 09:36.250
♪♪♪

09:36.333 --> 09:38.792
Ah. The two billion.

09:38.875 --> 09:41.125
I told them:
velvet rope.

09:41.208 --> 09:44.291
Spoken like a man who's still
mad he never got into Xenon.

09:44.375 --> 09:45.959
I'm on it, Taylor.

09:49.834 --> 09:52.041
This is clean. And it
does what you need,

09:52.125 --> 09:53.333
how you need. Tracks
it all in real time.

09:53.417 --> 09:54.917
We've also swept
the apartment.

09:55.000 --> 09:58.667
There are no listening devices,
no visual recording devices,

09:58.750 --> 10:01.000
no compromising
devices of any kind.

10:01.083 --> 10:03.709
But guests leave eyes and ears,
so we should sweep often.

10:03.792 --> 10:05.125
-The women.

10:05.208 --> 10:07.583
Wand them.

10:07.667 --> 10:09.041
He will.

10:09.125 --> 10:12.417
So, this is the Counter Intel
team, the new Halls.

10:14.125 --> 10:16.000
I don't think
they care for that.

10:16.083 --> 10:18.500
Why should I trust you
to do anything other than

10:18.583 --> 10:20.667
point me to the nearest
avocado toast?

10:20.750 --> 10:21.917
For whom have
you worked?

10:22.000 --> 10:23.667
Is this just a walk
on the wild side

10:23.750 --> 10:24.667
to spice up
the b

10:24.750 --> 10:28.375
How much you doing
this for the money?

10:28.458 --> 10:30.625
You can answer him.

10:30.709 --> 10:31.792
In re bona fides,
John built the code for

10:31.875 --> 10:35.375
four successful startups
in high school then Stanford,

10:35.458 --> 10:37.834
then was asked to travel to
71 countries for DARPA

10:37.917 --> 10:39.291
and Other Government Agency,

10:39.375 --> 10:40.875
all which he did
without complaint.

10:40.959 --> 10:42.500
And Timmy Dones
has a military background.

10:42.583 --> 10:44.709
What fucking war
were you in?

10:44.792 --> 10:46.709
Mr. Hall fought
the wars you've heard of.

10:46.792 --> 10:48.208
I fought the ones
you haven't.

10:48.291 --> 10:50.959
As for your other questions.
It's none of your business,

10:51.041 --> 10:53.417
smashed spring pea toast
is the new avocado toast,

10:53.500 --> 10:56.125
and 70 percent.

10:57.709 --> 11:00.291
Are we clear to talk
to Mr. Wagner going forward?

11:00.375 --> 11:02.458
Discuss anything except
women you care about.

11:06.542 --> 11:09.041
Yeah, so,
the two billion.

11:09.125 --> 11:11.917
Ah, and here I was thinking
you came to keep me company.

11:12.000 --> 11:15.166
Look, I know you're
giving it to outside funds,

11:15.250 --> 11:16.250
not on the surface.

11:16.333 --> 11:18.333
It'll get routed around
the world first,

11:18.417 --> 11:20.125
but then it will land
in certain funds,

11:20.208 --> 11:23.917
and suddenly they'll get hot
as Farrah Fawcett in '76.

11:24.000 --> 11:26.250
Don't do it.
One errant e-mail,

11:26.333 --> 11:28.583
one recorded call,
one trade that tracks back

11:28.667 --> 11:30.583
to you--and it's
Hassan chop!

11:30.667 --> 11:32.458
We're done. All of us.

11:32.542 --> 11:34.417
There's no need
for it, bwana.

11:34.500 --> 11:37.000
Satisfy your urges
some other way.

11:37.083 --> 11:38.709
Buy yourself something.

11:38.792 --> 11:40.583
I bought it all
already.

11:40.667 --> 11:41.959
Probably thrown it out.

11:42.041 --> 11:43.875
What about that vintage Cheetah
you've been eyeballing?

11:43.959 --> 11:46.959
Look, this is not a message
I'm born to carry.

11:47.041 --> 11:49.417
It goes against everything
I've built my life on.

11:49.500 --> 11:53.375
But for you, holding back
is essential right now.

11:53.458 --> 11:55.125
You're right about
hiding the money.

11:55.208 --> 11:56.667
That's too dangerous.
What if I didn't?

11:56.750 --> 11:59.792
-I could have Taylor move it,

11:59.875 --> 12:03.625
on-the-books, perfectly legal
disbursements to outside shops.

12:03.709 --> 12:06.375
Bobby--that's right, I'm not
calling you "Mr. President,"

12:06.458 --> 12:07.792
I'm calling you "Bobby"
because I've never used

12:07.875 --> 12:10.458
your first name
and I want to underline

12:10.542 --> 12:11.959
how serious this moment is.

12:12.041 --> 12:12.834
You've called me
Bobby before.

12:12.917 --> 12:15.542
Strategic mistake,
but not nearly as big

12:15.625 --> 12:18.166
as the one you're making
if you ask Taylor to do this.

12:18.250 --> 12:20.667
They have nothing
to gain by going along.

12:20.750 --> 12:21.917
They get to keep their
princely fucking job.

12:22.000 --> 12:25.166
If you fire them,
it will look like what it is.

12:25.250 --> 12:27.917
And you can't have it appear
you're illegally meddling.

12:28.000 --> 12:30.125
Especially when you're
illegally meddling.

12:30.208 --> 12:33.333
-My point--
-I get your point.

12:33.417 --> 12:35.542
So you won't take
the two billion?

12:35.625 --> 12:36.542
I get your point.

12:36.625 --> 12:39.750
Let's leave it at that.

12:41.709 --> 12:42.917
Ah!

12:43.000 --> 12:45.709
If it isn't George and Edward.

12:45.792 --> 12:48.417
Which one of you will give up
the throne for love?

12:48.500 --> 12:50.125
That seems like
a stupid reason.

12:50.208 --> 12:51.500
You must be George.

12:51.583 --> 12:53.667
Are you coming to our
game later, Uncle Wags?

12:53.750 --> 12:55.166
Is it official
Little League?

12:55.250 --> 12:57.875
-Yeah.
-Can't. Banned for life.

13:01.166 --> 13:03.667
Well, here we are on
the Axelrod case together,

13:03.750 --> 13:07.834
so, you know, we got our
fairy tale ending after all.

13:07.917 --> 13:09.834
You been working out? You look
like you've been working out.

13:09.917 --> 13:12.834
There's no good way
to answer that question.

13:12.917 --> 13:14.917
Is it ping pong?
You back at the tables?

13:15.000 --> 13:16.792
Uh, can I get a lawyer?

13:22.750 --> 13:26.000
Excuse me,
Ms. Gonzalez--

13:26.083 --> 13:28.041
Special Agent
Terri McCue, FBI.

13:28.125 --> 13:31.166
Uh,
me llamo Bryan Connerty,

13:31.250 --> 13:33.709
uh, Federal prosecutor.

13:33.792 --> 13:35.041
He's also
second alternate

13:35.125 --> 13:37.041
at the World Table Tennis
Championships.

13:37.125 --> 13:38.333
I'm really not...
that good.

13:38.417 --> 13:42.000
Ms. Gonzalez, we don't care
about your immigration status.

13:42.083 --> 13:43.375
That's not what we do.

13:43.458 --> 13:46.208
We may even be able to help you
if you cooperate with us.

13:46.291 --> 13:48.041
We want to speak to you about
your boss, Victor Mateo.

13:48.125 --> 13:51.208
Mr. Victor,
he's very good.

13:51.291 --> 13:52.917
He and his wife,
they sponsor me for

13:53.000 --> 13:54.792
the green card,
so I don't need help.

13:54.875 --> 13:56.583
You're not eligible
for a green card

13:56.667 --> 13:58.375
if you've committed a crime.

13:58.458 --> 14:00.750
A crime?
No. No, no, no.

14:00.834 --> 14:03.375
Let's put it up
on the colortini.

14:07.083 --> 14:11.166
That couple near you snapping
selfies were undercover agents.

14:11.250 --> 14:13.250
Mr. Victor
made me do it.

14:13.333 --> 14:17.583
Did Mr. Victor give you
the vial

14:17.667 --> 14:22.041
It was someone else. A woman.
But I know that it was for him.

14:22.125 --> 14:25.542
Him and his wife,
son monstruos.

14:25.625 --> 14:28.041
One time I drop a glass
licorera--Baccarat.

14:28.125 --> 14:33.208
Then Missus, she break the tail
light to my car to punish.

14:33.291 --> 14:36.208
I had to drive home afraid
that I get pulled over

14:36.291 --> 14:37.625
and sent back to Guatemala.

14:37.709 --> 14:39.041
Now I take the bus.

14:39.125 --> 14:42.458
I want to know how it worked.
When and where--

14:42.542 --> 14:44.709
The way that Mr. Victor and his
wife are--I can't be late.

14:44.792 --> 14:47.125
Or do I have
to tell them...

14:47.208 --> 14:48.792
No, no, no. Don't...
don't say anything.

14:48.875 --> 14:51.583
After work, you'll come
to my office

14:51.667 --> 14:55.500
and give a statement.

14:55.583 --> 14:57.875
Lo prometo.

15:02.709 --> 15:05.291
Yeah, what is it?

15:05.375 --> 15:07.250
My maid was late today.

15:07.333 --> 15:09.917
She's never late.

15:12.041 --> 15:16.291
We have a real problem.
We need to meet.

15:21.250 --> 15:22.333
Group of guys who
own this car,

15:22.417 --> 15:25.709
it's a smaller club than
the one that owns NBA teams,

15:25.792 --> 15:27.000
only 29 ever built.

15:27.083 --> 15:29.834
Which is exactly
why I'm buying it.

15:29.917 --> 15:32.000
Which is why I'm gonna
let you outbid me.

15:32.083 --> 15:33.375
Thanks.

15:33.458 --> 15:34.917
Sounds like you
want something.

15:35.000 --> 15:36.458
I do.

15:36.542 --> 15:38.166
I want in on
the new shit.

15:38.250 --> 15:41.333
You're raising money for
new ventures, count me in.

15:41.417 --> 15:45.000
Thanks, but I'm not looking
to give up any more equity.

15:47.250 --> 15:49.000
You're saying no
to money?

15:49.083 --> 15:50.709
Look, Axe, let me answer
the question you didn't ask,

15:50.792 --> 15:54.333
and this pains me to say...

15:54.417 --> 15:56.625
I don't want your  money.

15:56.709 --> 15:58.792
I've got too many eyes
on me, and I can't be

15:58.875 --> 16:00.792
anywhere near the shit show
you're in the middle of

16:00.875 --> 16:02.333
right now.

16:02.417 --> 16:06.875
Noted.

16:06.959 --> 16:11.875
