16:11.959 --> 16:13.208
Michael Panay.

16:13.291 --> 16:15.333
You haven't gone home
with a car this year.

16:15.417 --> 16:18.709
Is it the one you had your
heart set on all along?

16:18.792 --> 16:21.583
If Bill Thomas built a toaster,
I'd skip work to buy that.

16:21.667 --> 16:24.208
But you won't actually
buy this car, will you?

16:24.291 --> 16:27.583
Because you've been downsizing,
hoping no one would see.

16:28.709 --> 16:30.208
We're not downsizing.

16:30.291 --> 16:33.333
I was on the other side
of the Alperin trade.

16:33.417 --> 16:34.250
I know how much
you lost.

16:34.333 --> 16:36.875
Well, I know you're
not exactly trending

16:36.959 --> 16:38.875
in the right
direction, either.

16:38.959 --> 16:40.500
Maybe we help each other.

16:40.583 --> 16:42.083
I lead the early bidding,
knock out the dabblers,

16:42.166 --> 16:45.667
then you swoop in
at your desired price.

16:45.750 --> 16:46.709
What's your number?

16:46.792 --> 16:49.792
Mike, I'd pedal
the fucking Flintstones car

16:49.875 --> 16:52.125
before I went in
on this with you.

