17:06.375 --> 17:08.458
You sure?

17:08.542 --> 17:10.250
I know my people.

17:10.333 --> 17:12.250
She's been approached.

17:12.333 --> 17:14.959
I'll handle it.

17:15.041 --> 17:18.333
You know what this
means, don't you?

17:18.417 --> 17:20.625
They'll be coming
for the others.

17:28.291 --> 17:29.834
If that bursts into flame,

17:29.917 --> 17:31.625
I'm denouncing you
to Governor Danforth.

17:31.709 --> 17:33.125
It's a focus exercise.

17:33.208 --> 17:35.333
And Danforth is
just in the play.

17:35.417 --> 17:39.375
At the real Salem trials,
the judge was William Stoughton.

17:39.458 --> 17:42.959
Careful, that sounds like
something a witch would know.

17:43.041 --> 17:47.333
Also: We're looking good
on the two billion.

17:47.417 --> 17:50.166
Now that  got
you focused.

17:50.250 --> 17:52.625
I'm here to break
the glass.

17:53.959 --> 17:56.709
In case of
emergency, you know?

17:56.792 --> 17:59.500
Breathe, then talk.

17:59.583 --> 18:02.000
We're getting hit
by a tsunami.

18:02.083 --> 18:03.709
Shit.
Did the Fed hike--

18:03.792 --> 18:05.500
No. Actual tsunami.
In Brazil.

18:05.583 --> 18:07.667
No way. Brazil
doesn't have tsunamis.

18:07.750 --> 18:10.500
The worst they get
is ressacas do mar.

18:10.583 --> 18:12.834
"Sea hangover."

18:12.917 --> 18:15.667
Am I the only person here
who's loved a Portuguese woman?

18:15.750 --> 18:16.667
Brazil does not
normally have tsunamis.

18:16.750 --> 18:17.875
Black swan event.

18:17.959 --> 18:20.041
How heavy
are we in Brazil?

18:20.125 --> 18:21.709
Jim Morrison at the end.

18:21.792 --> 18:23.208
Our newly redeployed funds
are affected in dozens

18:23.291 --> 18:25.417
of different ways,
among the most notable,

18:25.500 --> 18:28.166
-Brazilian sugar and shipping.
-So we buy sugar futures.

18:28.250 --> 18:30.041
Impending shortage
means prices go up.

18:30.125 --> 18:32.125
Everyone will do that,
but sure.

18:32.208 --> 18:34.166
A few of the moves
I'm already making.

18:34.250 --> 18:36.917
Shorting Brazil's
largest debt holder,

18:37.000 --> 18:39.875
buying long-dated VIX calls.
Also buying solar, wind,

18:39.959 --> 18:41.750
and every
alternative energy play

18:41.834 --> 18:44.000
not dependent on
government subsidy.

18:45.917 --> 18:48.000
Um, is no one worried

18:48.083 --> 18:51.792
about the people,
you know, in  Brazil?

18:51.875 --> 18:54.417
If you want to pretend
you're concerned, see Wendy.

18:54.500 --> 18:56.041
He's not pretending, Wags.

18:56.125 --> 18:58.667
If you really care,
start a walk-a-thon.

18:58.750 --> 19:02.000
Tough Mudders are
the new walk-a-thons.

19:02.083 --> 19:04.375
But don't bring
that shit to me.

19:04.458 --> 19:08.792
Our own foundation was set up
for just these situations

19:08.875 --> 19:11.917
as a kind of emotional
and fiscal catch-all

19:12.000 --> 19:15.250
for you to use as a tool
for you to get

19:15.333 --> 19:17.250
your conscience out of the way.

19:17.333 --> 19:19.458
I wondered why you
showed at this meeting,

19:19.542 --> 19:21.208
you fucking vulture.

19:21.291 --> 19:23.834
What would salve my conscience
and my wallet is if I was

19:23.917 --> 19:25.250
a fucking contractor in Brazil.

19:25.333 --> 19:27.500
Too bad their leading
construction company's

19:27.583 --> 19:28.750
a scandal factory.

19:28.834 --> 19:31.083
Can't get into bed
with a firm that's had almost

19:31.166 --> 19:33.041
100 executives indicted.

19:33.125 --> 19:35.792
Our  principal
has been indicted.

19:37.834 --> 19:40.208
If it's a money-maker,
we do it.

19:40.291 --> 19:42.542
Legal trouble does
not mean you can't fulfill

19:42.625 --> 19:44.333
your teleological purpose.

19:44.417 --> 19:45.750
We're on the clock, people.

19:45.834 --> 19:48.709
Now's the time
to earn your paychecks.

19:53.417 --> 19:55.583
There's something
I always wondered:

19:55.667 --> 19:57.083
Why aren't you Charlie?

19:57.166 --> 19:58.166
-Feels like you would have

19:58.250 --> 20:01.417
-been a great Charlie.
-No, I agree.

20:01.500 --> 20:04.291
Oh, Charlie Rhoades, yeah,
that guy's yer best friend.

20:04.375 --> 20:05.375
-Yeah.

20:05.458 --> 20:08.917
Sure. Call ol' Charlie,
see if he can fill in, uh,

20:09.000 --> 20:10.291
as a fourth for tennis
or on a double date

20:10.375 --> 20:14.208
or just ride around
smashing mailboxes.

20:14.291 --> 20:16.625
Yeah. Charlie.
The best.

20:16.709 --> 20:21.417
But in our household,
my father was Charles.

20:21.500 --> 20:24.125
and every now
and then someone,

20:24.208 --> 20:26.166
business associate, the guy who
managed one of his buildings,

20:26.250 --> 20:29.458
who would get just
a little casual,

20:29.542 --> 20:32.000
accidentally let
a Charlie fly.

20:32.083 --> 20:35.291
The world would stop dead.

20:35.375 --> 20:39.208
"Do I look like a fucking
'Charlie' to you?"

20:42.291 --> 20:43.750
And that was that.

20:43.834 --> 20:46.542
The guy would piss himself,
and the day would continue.

20:46.625 --> 20:49.625
So, he was Charles,
and you were Chuck.

20:49.709 --> 20:52.041
And Good Time Charlie
was somewhere else

20:52.125 --> 20:54.792
out on the town
having all the laughs.

20:54.875 --> 20:58.208
Christ, man.

20:58.291 --> 21:01.625
Don't I know it.

21:01.709 --> 21:03.542
And how 'bout now?

21:03.625 --> 21:06.542
You just show up in my
chambers for the laughs.

21:06.625 --> 21:09.625
No. No.

21:11.166 --> 21:14.667
I am here in your chambers
to put myself in your debt.

21:14.750 --> 21:15.917
In my  debt.

21:16.000 --> 21:17.834
That's right.

21:17.917 --> 21:21.041
I was thinking back
to our last meal together,

21:21.125 --> 21:23.166
wherein you told me
I ought never mention

21:23.250 --> 21:25.291
the favor I had done you again.
And I promised then,

21:25.375 --> 21:28.375
and I intend to
keep that promise.

21:28.458 --> 21:32.000
And so I am here
to ask of you a favor,

21:32.083 --> 21:35.375
not as repayment to me
but the opposite.

21:35.458 --> 21:38.792
Oh, this must be big.

21:39.959 --> 21:42.375
Judge Funt is stepping
off the Axelrod case.

21:42.458 --> 21:43.959
No one knows.

21:44.041 --> 21:47.542
And when he does, Morgenstern
will make a special appointment

21:47.625 --> 21:52.208
of the judge who convinces
him he most wants the case.

21:52.291 --> 21:56.458
As often as not, that's
the first judge to ask.

21:56.542 --> 21:59.083
And you need
that to be me.

21:59.166 --> 22:01.709
We'll time it out
so it will be.

22:01.792 --> 22:03.792
Now, there are those
that would frame this

22:03.875 --> 22:07.000
as a favor for you,
because it's a marquee case.

22:07.083 --> 22:09.375
But I won't.

22:09.458 --> 22:11.166
You would be
doing me a service.

22:11.250 --> 22:13.208
And all you're asking
is that I be the judge,

22:13.291 --> 22:14.333
not that I rule
in Dake's favor,

22:14.417 --> 22:16.375
not that I'd be slanted
in any way.

22:16.458 --> 22:19.166
That's right.
It's that straightforward.

22:19.250 --> 22:20.875
Win. Lose. Draw.

22:20.959 --> 22:23.917
I want you on that bench because
I know you can't be bought.

22:24.000 --> 22:26.166
You can't be bent.
You can't be worked.

22:26.250 --> 22:27.417
Dake has a strong case.

22:27.500 --> 22:31.500
I want it heard fairly
and without prejudice.

22:33.083 --> 22:35.667
And if I grant
this request...

22:38.333 --> 22:40.083
There is nothing
you can ask me

22:40.166 --> 22:44.875
that I'll refuse you
for the rest of our days.

22:44.959 --> 22:48.458
If I agree, I would
take those words as gospel,

22:48.542 --> 22:52.458
Chuck. And I would
not be bashful to collect,

22:52.542 --> 22:54.583
should the need arise.

22:54.667 --> 22:58.125
I'd be honor bound
to deliver.

22:58.208 --> 23:00.709
That's too small a play.
It won't save us.

23:00.792 --> 23:02.125
Keep looking.

23:06.667 --> 23:09.792
Axe would be out on that
floor screaming at them

23:09.875 --> 23:11.792
like Gordon Ramsay
until they delivered.

23:11.875 --> 23:13.625
Hm. You're more
Alton Brown.

23:13.709 --> 23:15.875
The ideas they're bringing...
Some deployable,

23:15.959 --> 23:18.208
some useful as a benchmark
of what other firms

23:18.291 --> 23:20.375
will be thinking and how
we need to do better,

23:20.458 --> 23:23.750
but none platonically good.

23:23.834 --> 23:25.959
Your first round
of investments coinciding

23:26.041 --> 23:28.750
with your first crisis.

23:28.834 --> 23:30.625
That would be
a lot for anybody.

23:30.709 --> 23:34.458
Axe was already considering
sidecarring two billion.

23:34.542 --> 23:38.458
And you think today will
make the decision for him.

23:38.542 --> 23:41.625
I am acutely aware of
the way people look at me.

23:41.709 --> 23:44.667
I have cultivated, through
achievement and discipline,

23:44.750 --> 23:47.917
a mystique that compensates
for my lack of track record.

23:48.000 --> 23:49.625
A loss shatters that,

23:49.709 --> 23:52.417
and with it the confidence
of everyone who works here.

23:52.500 --> 23:56.000
In their eyes--in Axe's eyes--
I become simply inexperienced.

23:56.083 --> 23:57.000
I can't let that happen.

23:57.083 --> 24:00.000
That's why I need to get
through today unscathed.

24:00.083 --> 24:02.166
The way you
think Axe would.

24:04.333 --> 24:08.875
It's important in your job that
you face unpleasant realities.

24:08.959 --> 24:10.667
Axe Capital may lose money
today,

24:10.750 --> 24:12.083
probably will.

24:13.208 --> 24:16.291
You know that, right?

24:18.625 --> 24:20.375
No.

