companies are down for

31:13.875 --> 31:16.000
the count, these guys will
have a shot at a monopoly.

31:16.083 --> 31:18.792
-We should buy in two days.
-Four days, when it bottoms.

31:18.875 --> 31:21.375
But this is going to help
dig us out a little more.

31:21.458 --> 31:22.709
Good work.

31:27.125 --> 31:29.375
Will you make sure Axe
knows it came from me?

31:29.458 --> 31:32.125
Why would you think we're
communicating about trades?

31:32.208 --> 31:33.291
What?

31:33.375 --> 31:34.583
That would be illegal.

31:34.667 --> 31:38.333
I know. But...

31:38.417 --> 31:40.125
What are you
saying about me?

31:40.208 --> 31:42.417
What are you saying
about the place you work?

31:42.500 --> 31:44.792
Actually, if he hates it,
that would be worse.

31:44.875 --> 31:47.625
Don't say anything.

31:47.709 --> 31:49.875
It is now 1:47
on the 9th day of...

31:53.291 --> 31:55.375
I'm sitting in my office,
which I paid for,

31:55.458 --> 31:56.959
seeing how things
run without me.

31:57.041 --> 31:58.208
Won't work.

31:58.291 --> 31:59.667
People are afraid
to take chances

31:59.750 --> 32:01.000
with you here.
To be wrong.

32:01.083 --> 32:03.625
Or they want a slap on the ass
from you. Which you can't give.

32:03.709 --> 32:04.709
Move over, Zapruder.
I got this.

32:04.792 --> 32:06.834
Actually, I think this
falls within my dominion,

32:06.917 --> 32:10.667
and the stick can be
really tricky for noobs--

32:12.625 --> 32:15.792
Hmm.
Guess it was tricky.

32:15.875 --> 32:20.750
Why didn't you anticipate
the tsunami?

32:20.834 --> 32:22.375
Maybe I should have
when that

32:22.458 --> 32:24.875
underground earthquake
hit off Mozambique.

32:24.959 --> 32:29.000
Strange conditions
bring strange results.

32:29.083 --> 32:30.709
That's what
brought this on.

32:30.792 --> 32:33.500
You knew right then
but you couldn't act.

32:33.583 --> 32:34.667
Maybe you would have
used your experience

32:34.750 --> 32:37.000
to think more globally.

32:37.083 --> 32:38.667
Maybe you would have been
cautious. De-risked.

32:38.750 --> 32:41.041
The mature move.

32:41.125 --> 32:42.083
Is that a dig?

32:42.166 --> 32:42.792
It's not.

32:42.875 --> 32:45.250
You have
more experience.

32:45.333 --> 32:48.375
You connect points
I don't even know to look for.

32:48.458 --> 32:51.792
I understand how hard it is
to have things inside you

32:51.875 --> 32:53.500
that you can't
communicate.

32:53.583 --> 32:56.542
I can't imagine how hard it must
be to know how to say them

32:56.625 --> 32:57.959
and still not
be allowed to.

32:58.041 --> 33:01.375
And yet,
you are not allowed to.

33:01.458 --> 33:02.500
Have you heard me
direct any trades?

33:02.583 --> 33:05.041
The people out there don't
know who they're looking to.

33:05.125 --> 33:08.291
Since it can't be you,
it needs to be me.

33:15.583 --> 33:18.291
If you can't live with that,
I can be the one who leaves.

33:18.375 --> 33:20.792
You'll probably make up
the losses but get yourself

33:20.875 --> 33:22.875
banned for life or worse.

33:25.333 --> 33:27.500
I'm leaving,

33:27.583 --> 33:30.458
and I'm taking
the two billion.

33:30.542 --> 33:34.709
I'll send instructions shortly
about what to do with it.

33:37.125 --> 33:40.375
And at 1:53 p.m.,

33:40.458 --> 33:43.583
Robert Axelrod...

33:43.667 --> 33:44.291
has left the building.

33:46.500 --> 33:47.500
I'm glad I caught you.

33:47.583 --> 33:49.417
You wouldn't have
if my fucking car guy

33:49.500 --> 33:50.959
could time his job right.

33:51.041 --> 33:54.291
Yeah, George Washington had the
same problem leaving Trenton.

33:54.375 --> 33:55.583
Wags told you?

33:55.667 --> 33:58.250
Texted me while you were
rampaging through the office.

33:58.333 --> 34:00.458
I wasn't rampaging.
I was inspiring.

34:00.542 --> 34:02.125
You know Washington
didn't actually

34:02.208 --> 34:04.625
-Of course.

34:04.709 --> 34:07.583
Structurally unsound, and he'd
have made himself a target.

34:07.667 --> 34:09.959
Yet you worry
about neither.

34:11.917 --> 34:15.917
It's hard to
shut it off, Wend.

34:16.000 --> 34:17.792
I know.

34:17.875 --> 34:21.834
But if you can't, you will
lose the battle and the war.

34:25.792 --> 34:27.375
Do you want me
to come with you?

34:27.458 --> 34:29.083
Stay here with Taylor.

34:29.166 --> 34:32.667
They need some senior
officer for back up.

34:37.417 --> 34:40.208
You're fired.

34:40.875 --> 34:43.458
Find out when Judge Funt's
court is in recess.

34:43.542 --> 34:43.959
Yep.

34:45.625 --> 34:47.250
A Mr. Allerd
is here for you.

34:49.875 --> 34:54.000
I'm Karl Allerd,
your new AUSA.

34:54.083 --> 34:56.875
I think I'd remember if I hired
a new line prosecutor.

34:56.959 --> 35:00.625
Remember when Dake said
there'd be a favor to be named?

35:01.834 --> 35:03.667
Ah.

35:03.750 --> 35:05.375
You're the favor.

35:06.875 --> 35:08.709
You don't trust me.

35:08.792 --> 35:10.500
Hell, I wouldn't
from your chair.

35:10.583 --> 35:12.792
A Spy In the House Of Lords
and so forth. Yes.

35:12.875 --> 35:15.375
So I'll earn your trust.

35:15.458 --> 35:16.333
Will you?

35:16.417 --> 35:17.000
I look forward to
seeing that trick.

35:17.083 --> 35:18.250
That'll be
a neat trick.

35:18.333 --> 35:20.959
Ms. Sacker, our Head of Crim,
will get you situated.

35:21.041 --> 35:22.166
-Mm.

35:22.250 --> 35:22.417
Mm, I will.

35:27.417 --> 35:28.333
Hey, I've been
revising my idea.

35:28.417 --> 35:30.959
There's a division
of a struggling company

35:31.041 --> 35:32.417
in Thailand, that I think--

35:32.500 --> 35:33.291
Wait, is this
the sugar company?

35:33.375 --> 35:35.917
Is it, is this
the same damn deal?

35:36.000 --> 35:37.875
No...It's just
one facet of the company

35:37.959 --> 35:39.875
that I think could be
promising to look into.

35:39.959 --> 35:41.375
It started out as a family
business, and...

35:41.458 --> 35:42.542
-So this is--
this is the same deal.

35:42.625 --> 35:43.458
-Not really--
-Kimmy,

35:43.542 --> 35:48.208
this piece of shit
ain't Axe Cap.

36:03.959 --> 36:06.041
What are you
working on?

36:06.125 --> 36:07.250
Nothing.

36:12.583 --> 36:16.500
I want to see all Ben Kim's
search results for the day.

36:16.583 --> 36:17.959
You mean, like,
browser results, or...

36:18.041 --> 36:21.542
Everything
he did today.

36:22.667 --> 36:24.333
Hey, you
on your way home?

36:24.417 --> 36:25.375
Nope.

36:25.458 --> 36:26.375
Chief.
You got to get on your way

36:26.458 --> 36:28.125
if you want to make it
in time to take

36:28.208 --> 36:31.166
the princelings
to Little League.

36:31.917 --> 36:33.750
Have Bruce take 'em.

36:33.834 --> 36:36.583
You got it.

36:47.000 --> 36:48.625
He's been home
three weekends this year.

36:48.709 --> 36:52.458
I'm almost positive one of them
was his assistant's mistake.

36:52.542 --> 36:54.667
And he assumes I never
say anything about him

36:54.750 --> 36:58.417
fucking his way through
the entire New York pool.

36:58.500 --> 37:01.291
But if you can leave Axe...

37:01.375 --> 37:03.875
You give me courage, Lara.

37:06.917 --> 37:09.625
You're smart, Lilly.

37:09.709 --> 37:11.166
You had a career
for a second.

37:11.250 --> 37:14.750
You know your shopper
isn't your friend,

37:14.834 --> 37:17.458
personal trainer doesn't think
you're actually making progress,

37:17.542 --> 37:21.417
and all the charities you give
money to don't actually

37:21.500 --> 37:23.375
honor you when
they honor you.

37:23.458 --> 37:26.291
But on some level,
you believe every bit of it.

37:26.375 --> 37:31.041
You think the attention
you receive is deserved.

37:31.125 --> 37:34.125
But when that fades,
when every relationship

37:34.208 --> 37:37.250
in your life reveals itself
to be a trade on your husband's

37:37.333 --> 37:40.792
net worth, you may say
"Fuck false friends,"

37:40.875 --> 37:42.458
but you'll be hiring
a PR rep the first time

37:42.542 --> 37:47.041
your Halloween costume
isn't mentioned in Page Six.

37:48.583 --> 37:51.250
So keep your
own courage, Lilly.

37:51.333 --> 37:54.333
And while you're at it,
consider keeping that husband.

37:54.417 --> 37:57.166
Because while he may not give
you what you think you want,

37:57.250 --> 38:00.166
he lets you keep on
being Mrs. Keith Currier Smith,

38:00.250 --> 38:02.750
and I'm pretty sure
that's what you need.

38:02.834 --> 38:05.375
Now you're trying
to decide whether

38:05.458 --> 38:06.834
to be pissed
or grateful.

38:06.917 --> 38:08.792
Definitely grateful.

38:21.250 --> 38:22.875
Whoa!

38:32.041 --> 38:34.625
Here you go.

38:34.709 --> 38:36.542
Have fun.

38:36.625 --> 38:38.500
Thanks, Bruce.

38:44.625 --> 38:46.792
♪ dramatic music  ♪

38:46.875 --> 38:51.667
♪♪♪

38:51.750 --> 38:52.375
We got your
latest request.

38:52.458 --> 38:54.709
It's a big lift.
Hard transfer.

38:54.792 --> 38:57.083
International withdrawals
and deposits like this

38:57.166 --> 38:58.667
do not get done same day.

38:58.750 --> 39:00.250
-It's not the sort of thing

39:00.333 --> 39:03.583
most clients ask for. Especially
not when they're drawing heat.

39:03.667 --> 39:05.250
These are my needs.

39:05.333 --> 39:09.291
Either you meet them
or you can't.

39:09.375 --> 39:12.250
We can get it done. But this
isn't a reusable pipeline.

39:12.333 --> 39:14.291
Fine by me.

39:14.375 --> 39:18.875
♪♪♪

39:18.959 --> 39:20.417
She's supposed
to be here by 5:30.

39:20.500 --> 39:22.583
-It's already--
-I know what time it is.

39:22.667 --> 39:24.166
Call it in.

39:28.417 --> 39:30.250
I'd like to have
a person of interest

39:30.333 --> 39:32.750
picked up.
Gonzalez, Maria.

39:32.834 --> 39:35.417
No Social.

39:35.500 --> 39:36.625
Yeah.

39:36.709 --> 39:39.959
D.O.B. 1/22/79.

39:40.041 --> 39:41.041
You think
she got cold feet?

39:41.125 --> 39:44.834
I think that's best case.

39:44.917 --> 39:47.792
You have her already.
That's great news. Where?

39:49.208 --> 39:50.625
Hold her. She's mine.

39:50.709 --> 39:52.458
She got picked up
in an ICE sweep.

39:52.542 --> 39:55.625
She's currently at the Varick
Street Detention Center.

40:11.500 --> 40:13.291
Are you gonna
bring Maria?

40:13.375 --> 40:15.458
She's right there.

40:18.041 --> 40:19.041
Who is that?

40:19.125 --> 40:22.000
Maria Gonzalez.

40:22.083 --> 40:23.709
That may be
a  Maria Gonzalez,

40:23.792 --> 40:25.500
but that is not
our  Maria Gonzalez.

40:25.583 --> 40:27.333
That is the wrong
Maria Gonzalez.

40:27.417 --> 40:29.834
Do you have someone else
here with that name?

40:31.500 --> 40:34.792
We did until she was
put on a goodbye charter

40:34.875 --> 40:36.959
from Newark Liberty.

40:38.291 --> 40:41.375
It's got to be some
bureaucratic screw-up.

40:41.458 --> 40:42.125
No, it doesn't.

40:43.458 --> 40:45.375
Somebody knew she was
gonna be picked up

40:45.458 --> 40:49.750
before we did
and got to her info.

40:52.417 --> 40:54.208
This has Axe
written all over it.

40:54.291 --> 40:57.834
♪ dramatic music  ♪

40:57.917 --> 41:02.709
♪♪♪

41:02.792 --> 41:07.458
♪♪♪

41:09.625 --> 41:12.625
They deported the wrong
Maria Gonzalez.

41:12.709 --> 41:16.000
Our witness is on a plane
that lands in 90 minutes.

41:16.083 --> 41:18.750
We need her met on the ground
in Guatemala and returned.

41:18.834 --> 41:22.709
There are a lot of, uh,
high-level, deeply uncomfortable

41:22.792 --> 41:27.250
calls required to make
that happen. DOJ. DHS. State.

41:27.333 --> 41:29.291
And they all start
with your boss.

41:29.375 --> 41:31.542
I really don't want to call
the Attorney General about this.

41:31.625 --> 41:36.542
He's publicly stated
this case matters to him.

41:37.875 --> 41:42.125
Ollie, you're a bit of
a rara avis,  aren't you?

41:42.208 --> 41:44.834
You got no "hat,"
no one looking out for you,

41:44.917 --> 41:47.458
and yet you have risen.

41:47.542 --> 41:50.417
Maybe it's because you
have an immaculate record.

41:50.500 --> 41:53.000
Some guys don't trust
immaculate record.

41:53.083 --> 41:55.208
I do. I have
an immaculate record.

41:55.291 --> 41:58.333
Thank you, General.

41:58.417 --> 42:00.542
That was from a movie.

42:00.625 --> 42:02.500
You don't watch movies,
do you, Ollie?

42:02.583 --> 42:06.917
I re-watch The Decalogue
every year.

42:07.000 --> 42:08.917
Uh, well, I read
what you sent me.

42:09.000 --> 42:13.083
Just to make sure I have it
straight: We got the wrong Guad?

42:13.166 --> 42:16.083
That is indeed
the case.

42:16.166 --> 42:17.625
Say it.

42:20.291 --> 42:24.250
We got the wrong Guad.

42:24.333 --> 42:27.542
But Maria Gonzalez,
our Maria Gonzalez,

42:27.625 --> 42:28.625
is a key cooperator.

42:28.709 --> 42:31.667
We need her back.
And since this is

42:31.750 --> 42:33.250
an extraordinary situation--

42:33.333 --> 42:34.792
Well, in one respect.

42:34.875 --> 42:37.625
In another, it's just the way
things are supposed to go.

42:37.709 --> 42:39.625
The right Maria Gonzalez came
into this country illegally,

42:39.709 --> 42:44.500
she stayed illegally,
and she committed a fraud

42:44.583 --> 42:47.250
on the stockholders of that
snake-bit juice company.

42:47.333 --> 42:49.709
She is three times illegal.

42:49.792 --> 42:54.667
That makes her removable,
and she was removed.

42:57.250 --> 42:58.583
Um...

42:58.667 --> 43:00.083
Next time...

43:00.166 --> 43:04.458
instead of asking me
to undo your fuck-up,

43:04.542 --> 43:07.542
maybe just see to it that
the situation remains like

43:07.625 --> 43:10.083
our holy Mother of Mercy,
blessedly un-fucked.

43:19.750 --> 43:21.417
How'd that go?

43:25.083 --> 43:26.834
Does Axe ever hesitate?

43:27.166 --> 43:28.500
Why?

43:28.583 --> 43:31.750
I'm hesitating.
Can't pull the trigger.

43:31.834 --> 43:34.500
Markets are closed.
Overseas play?

43:34.583 --> 43:37.250
Ben Kim found
a big opportunity in Thailand.

43:37.333 --> 43:40.125
A troubled public company
with a promising sugar division.

43:40.208 --> 43:42.333
He spotted a good target
but just couldn't quite

43:42.417 --> 43:44.458
figure out how to hit it--
or didn't have the courage

43:44.542 --> 43:45.709
to shoot at it.

43:45.792 --> 43:49.041
We need to keep working
with him on that.

43:49.125 --> 43:50.208
But you see the play?

43:50.291 --> 43:53.166
Yes. A PIPE. Private investment
in public equity.

43:53.250 --> 43:55.291
Basically, we take
ownership of a spin-off,

43:55.375 --> 43:56.375
and a commission
from brokering its sale.

43:56.458 --> 43:59.000
So, why the hesitation?

43:59.083 --> 44:02.000
It will be the single largest
investment I've made as CIO,

44:02.083 --> 44:04.250
and a type Axe Cap
has never made before.

44:04.333 --> 44:07.041
If you make this move, where
do you end up for the day?

44:07.125 --> 44:08.709
Unscathed?

44:11.458 --> 44:14.583
This would
lock in a loss.

44:14.667 --> 44:19.542
Yes. The high-reward plays
are all high-risk.

44:19.625 --> 44:21.250
It's good you can't
run it by Axe.

44:22.875 --> 44:27.458
Forces you to hear
your own voice and trust it.

44:28.667 --> 44:33.291
You'll probably
do the right thing.

44:33.375 --> 44:36.458
And when the day comes you get
one wrong, that'll be good, too.

44:36.542 --> 44:39.000
Because I'll realize I'm mortal
and it's not so bad?

44:39.083 --> 44:40.750
Because it'll be
fucking horrible

44:40.834 --> 44:44.208
and you'll do anything you can
to avoid that feeling again.

44:54.500 --> 44:55.875
Hey.

44:57.834 --> 45:00.166
You know what, Bobby?

45:00.250 --> 45:02.959
I'm gonna do you
a favor:

45:03.041 --> 45:04.959
You're off the hook.

45:05.041 --> 45:08.417
If you don't want 50-50 custody,
you don't need to have it.

45:08.500 --> 45:10.500
I can tell other people
it's 50-50,

45:10.583 --> 45:13.208
and I can come up with something
to tell the boys, too.

45:13.291 --> 45:15.625
Why the fuck do you think
I don't want the kids?

45:15.709 --> 45:18.750
You had them for one day,
at a time when you don't

45:18.834 --> 45:22.625
have to go to work,
and you ditched them.

45:22.709 --> 45:24.875
You let them be airlifted
into Little League.

45:24.959 --> 45:26.458
I mean, it was mortifying.

45:26.542 --> 45:28.041
I didn't mean
to embarrass them.

45:28.125 --> 45:30.792
They weren't embarrassed.

45:30.875 --> 45:34.166
They didn't know to be,
which is a whole other thing.

45:34.250 --> 45:37.875
You know, I don't know if you
need to work on your case

45:37.959 --> 45:39.750
or go on a trip

45:39.834 --> 45:42.917
or become
a fucking cobbler,

45:43.000 --> 45:47.542
but it doesn't seem like
you are where you need to be.

45:49.583 --> 45:52.250
And I'd offer to help,
but my help doesn't seem

45:52.333 --> 45:53.375
to be what you want, either.

45:53.458 --> 45:57.333
♪ dramatic music  ♪

45:57.417 --> 46:02.166
♪♪♪

46:02.250 --> 46:06.417
♪♪♪

46:08.083 --> 46:10.250
I have everything positioned
and ready,

46:10.333 --> 46:13.375
and yet...

46:13.458 --> 46:16.000
Judge Funt still has
the case on his docket.

46:16.083 --> 46:19.667
My bag is packed, but I can't
seem to walk out the door.

46:19.750 --> 46:24.291
If I fail at this,
everything is dashed.

46:24.375 --> 46:27.709
For then
I will have ruined myself

46:27.792 --> 46:29.375
in his eyes

46:29.458 --> 46:33.250
and  exposed my position.

46:33.333 --> 46:37.583
Only a fool doesn't
look at the downside.

46:37.667 --> 46:38.750
But only a coward allows
it to dissuade him

46:38.834 --> 46:43.208
from that which he knows
he must do.

46:43.291 --> 46:45.083
I know
you're not a coward.

46:45.166 --> 46:48.834
I don't like the sound of that
word coming out of your mouth.

46:48.917 --> 46:51.208
Neither do I.

46:51.291 --> 46:54.917
I'll see you
at home. After.

47:02.333 --> 47:05.208
Chuck?

47:06.959 --> 47:10.667
No one takes
this shortcut anymore.

47:10.750 --> 47:12.417
This isn't
your courthouse.

47:12.500 --> 47:14.875
Are you lost?

47:14.959 --> 47:19.333
Oh, right where
I need to be, Judge Funt,

47:19.417 --> 47:22.417
which is, unfortunately,
in your way.

47:24.166 --> 47:24.583
Ah.

47:24.667 --> 47:28.083
The Axelrod case.

47:28.166 --> 47:32.375
You had to know a day
like this would come.

47:32.458 --> 47:34.000
I never asked you...

47:34.083 --> 47:35.041
You didn't have to.

47:38.166 --> 47:41.041
Your son's doing
well, I hope,

47:41.125 --> 47:43.250
made the most
of his medical career.

47:45.542 --> 47:47.583
Yeah, he's
a good doctor.

47:47.667 --> 47:49.500
That's what
I wanted for him.

47:51.250 --> 47:54.500
If he hadn't have supplied
those future sons of Hippocrates

47:54.583 --> 47:57.583
with Adderall, some
other med student would have.

47:57.667 --> 48:00.125
I won't let you
dictate my rulings.

48:00.208 --> 48:05.959
The bench cannot be tainted
by personal debts.

48:06.041 --> 48:08.959
Name another favor.

48:09.041 --> 48:11.959
I know that this is the biggest
case that you've ever drawn.

48:12.041 --> 48:14.750
Well, that's something that you
would think about in my shoes,

48:14.834 --> 48:16.625
but I don't.

48:16.709 --> 48:20.583
No, you wouldn't.

48:20.667 --> 48:23.500
And you wouldn't hide
in a hallway waiting

48:23.583 --> 48:25.792
to pounce when I walked by.

48:26.917 --> 48:29.166
But I am not
the man you are.

48:34.208 --> 48:36.792
Oh.

48:36.875 --> 48:39.792
You're not here to ask me
to shade my rulings.

48:39.875 --> 48:43.000
You're here to ask me
to step off it.

48:43.083 --> 48:46.792
It's a hard laydown. And
I'm asking you to lay it down.

48:49.417 --> 48:51.375
Ask yourself

48:51.458 --> 48:54.750
who you
really are, Chuck.

48:54.834 --> 48:57.041
Are you the man that's
reduced to collecting debts

48:57.125 --> 49:01.333
of the soul like--
like old Mr. Scratch?

49:01.417 --> 49:03.709
Well, as with all stories
about that being,

49:03.792 --> 49:07.458
the debt is due, even if,
especially if,

49:07.542 --> 49:11.542
it is not fair or even
right to collect it.

49:13.750 --> 49:18.542
Believe me, my...my insides
hurt making this request.

49:18.625 --> 49:21.333
Oh, I don't believe
that even a little.

49:21.417 --> 49:23.041
You like your insides
just as they are.

49:23.125 --> 49:26.917
You want to be right here,
making these moves.

49:27.000 --> 49:31.333
You need that feeling in your
stomach to know you're alive.

49:33.959 --> 49:37.333
I really think
I am sorry.

49:37.417 --> 49:39.166
Fuck you, Chuck!

49:44.750 --> 49:48.208
I'll recuse myself.

49:50.125 --> 49:52.250
My tab is clear.

