50:14.375 --> 50:17.125
and ask for a personal loan?

50:17.208 --> 50:21.125
I just heard DeGiulio is the new
judge on the Axelrod case.

50:21.208 --> 50:23.208
Not our dream judge,
but fair-minded,

50:23.291 --> 50:26.792
likely to hew closely to
the law, rule narrowly.

50:26.875 --> 50:29.250
That'll favor us
a lot more than Funt.

50:29.333 --> 50:31.000
Well, then,

50:31.083 --> 50:33.417
I guess it's a gift.

50:33.500 --> 50:36.291
Chuck.

50:36.375 --> 50:39.166
I know his fingerprints.

50:41.500 --> 50:43.709
Are you gonna do
something about this?

50:43.792 --> 50:46.709
I'm not in the habit
of rejecting gifts.

50:50.041 --> 50:53.333
Do you know about
White Day in Japan?

50:53.417 --> 50:56.792
Over there on Valentine's Day,
women buy presents

50:56.875 --> 51:00.166
for their salarymen bosses,
and those presents are displayed

51:00.250 --> 51:02.250
for all to see, so the most
important thing is the size.

51:02.333 --> 51:06.041
That's how others know
that the recipient is valued.

51:06.125 --> 51:08.959
A month later, on White Day,
the men give a return gift

51:09.041 --> 51:11.250
of two to three
times the value.

51:11.333 --> 51:16.500
So if there's a salaryman
you don't respect,

51:16.583 --> 51:19.041
you get him something
small but expensive.

51:25.125 --> 51:28.166
Chuck just gave you
diamond cufflinks,

51:28.250 --> 51:31.458
and when White Day comes,
you're gonna have to give him

51:31.542 --> 51:34.000
something that costs
a lot more.

